INSTALL:

1. Download the latest version of OXID eShop Community Edition here:
   http://www.oxid-esales.com/de/download/open-source-software-oxid-eshop-community-edition
2. Create a new directory on your computer and unpack the downloaded file there
3. Upload the files to your web server using an FTP client of your choice
4. Check if your server environment meets our system requirements:
   http://www.oxid-esales.com/en/products/community-edition/system-requirements
5. Create a new database on your server and note all given data (db-host, db-name and db-password)
6. Open your browser on http://www.yourshopurl.com and follow the installation instructions.

NOTE: In any case of hassle, turn to ‘Installation and configuration’ section our community forum:
http://www.oxid-esales.com/en/resources/forum/

Have fun!
